Absolutely! Hereâ€™s a simple HTML code snippet to design a basic webpage. This example includes a header, a navigation menu, a main content area, and a footer.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Simple Webpage</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        header {
            background: #35424a;
            color: #ffffff;
            padding: 10px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        nav {
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        nav a {
            margin: 0 15px;
            color: #35424a;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        main {
            padding: 20px;
            background: #ffffff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px 0;
            background: #35424a;
            color: #ffffff;
            position: relative;
            bottom: 0;
            width: 100%;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Welcome to My Webpage</h1>
</header>

<nav>
    <a href="#home">Home</a>
    <a href="#about">About</a>
    <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
</nav>

<main>
    <h2>About This Page</h2>
    <p>This is a simple webpage designed to demonstrate basic HTML structure and styling.</p>
</main>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2024 My Simple Webpage</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **Header**: Contains the title of the webpage.
- **Navigation**: Links to different sections (you can add more links as needed).
- **Main Content**: A section for your main content.
- **Footer**: Displays copyright information.

You can copy this code into a text editor and save it with a `.html` extension (e.g., `index.html`). Then, open it in a web browser to see your webpage!

Feel free to modify the content and styles to suit your needs. What kind of webpage are you looking to create?
